title: Merge pull request #96 from eighthave/master
message:
Merge pull request #96 from eighthave/master

boring build system stuff

title: remove gradle.properties from git, everything is commmented out
message:
remove gradle.properties from git, everything is commmented out

This gradle.properties does not set anything, everything is commented out,
so it does not need to be in git.  Having it in git means that when Android
Studio reformats it on someone's machine, it'll show up as a change in
`git status` and git GUIs.

title: remove Android Studio files from git
message:
remove Android Studio files from git

everything in .idea/ and all .iml files should not be included in git. They
are generated by Android Studio when opening a gradle project.  They will
be different for each person's Android Studio, so if they are in git, it'll
be an endless source of git conflicts.

Android Studio will recreate all of these files from the gradle files if
you do "Open an Existing Android Studio project"

title: use gradle witness to verify included jars
message:
use gradle witness to verify included jars

This makes sure that the downloaded jars match what the original developer
saw.

The gradle-witness.jar comes from Signal, since Whisper Systems wrote
gradle witness:
https://github.com/WhisperSystems/Signal-Android/raw/a9637baddf22bed58c6dba18ee39ffc543a0751e/libs/gradle-witness.jar

title: make ./gradlew verify the gradle binary it downloads
message:
make ./gradlew verify the gradle binary it downloads

This just makes sure that the downloaded binary matches the official
release binary, i.e. has no malware in it.  Also, the -all package is not
needed to run the build, only the smaller -bin is required.

The gradle-wrapper.jar was copied from the open-keychain project, since
they know this stuff better than me :)
https://github.com/open-keychain/open-keychain/raw/92d2a052f1e660f498294bdb57f1237ae81fc770/gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.jar

title: respond to generic panic trigger Intent by logging out
message:
respond to generic panic trigger Intent by logging out

PanicKit provides a common framework for creating "panic button" apps that
can trigger actions in "panic responder" apps.  In this case, the response
is to log out in the app.
